One year ago, during Lunar New Year celebrations in Monterey Park, California, 11 innocent people were killed in a mass shooting. This tragedy deeply affected the Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander communities. Two days later, another mass shooting occurred in Half Moon Bay, California, where seven people were killed. The article mentions that President Biden and his wife, Jill, expressed their condolences and visited the affected communities. The President also announced new actions to address gun violence, including the establishment of the White House Office of Gun Violence Prevention and the implementation of the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act. California has passed over 20 new gun safety laws, and the article calls for other states to follow suit. The article emphasizes the need for Congress to take action, including banning assault weapons, implementing universal background checks, and requiring safe storage of guns. It criticizes Republicans in Congress for not taking action on gun violence.